        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1590428648" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2814002716031164276">This story captured me from the beginning and I found myself reading it in one day. Being pulled into the story of Sara and the amazing ability that she develops, I found myself unable to stop reading until I knew how it ended. And I can honestly say, there were many parts of this story that filled my body with chills. Yes I got the chills and I shed a few tears. <br/>Sara Hopkins has amazing faith in God for a small child and that faith leads her to experience and share God&apos;s touch. With her faith, </span>
  <span id="freeText2814002716031164276" style="display:none">This story captured me from the beginning and I found myself reading it in one day. Being pulled into the story of Sara and the amazing ability that she develops, I found myself unable to stop reading until I knew how it ended. And I can honestly say, there were many parts of this story that filled my body with chills. Yes I got the chills and I shed a few tears. <br />Sara Hopkins has amazing faith in God for a small child and that faith leads her to experience and share God's touch. With her faith, she touches and changes the small town of White Dove. <br /><br />"I think Jesus comes to everyone. But we have to see Him in our own way, don't we?" <br /><br /><br />Filled with well thought out characters, detailed scenes and an ending that will leave you thinking about it for days, The Mustard Seed is a must read. I received this book for free for purposes of review. All opinions are my own.<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="2814002716031164276" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

